    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Between the Conventions, Lieberman Is Topic A</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Carl Holmes reply to Aug 9 letter holds Sen Joseph I Lieberman was correct to both score Pres Clinton's relationship with Monica S Lewinsky and vote to acquit him in Senate impeachment trial</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>An Aug. 9 letter writer charges  Senator Joseph I. Lieberman with political expediency in voting to acquit President Clinton in the Senate impeachment trial.</p>
        <p>Because he is a devout man, Senator Lieberman's public rebuke of the president's relationship with Monica S. Lewinsky was appropriate and understandable.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>An Aug. 9 letter writer charges  Senator Joseph I. Lieberman with political expediency in voting to acquit President Clinton in the Senate impeachment trial.</p>
        <p>Because he is a devout man, Senator Lieberman's public rebuke of the president's relationship with Monica S. Lewinsky was appropriate and understandable.</p>
        <p>But as a competent lawyer, Mr. Lieberman also recognized that the presidential lapse was neither treason nor bribery, nor the high crime or misdemeanor contemplated by the learned men who drafted Article II of the Constitution.</p>
        <p>CARL HOLMES  Jamaica, Queens, Aug. 9, 2000  The writer is a lawyer.</p>
      </block>
